# 6. 雨と夕暮れ

Saki: It's raining...
Saki: My fever's pretty much gone...
Saki: But there's no point in going to the observatory now. We wouldn't be able to see anything with this weather.
Saki: ...
Tsukasa's Voice: Saki, breakfast is ready. There's even that hot chocolate you like. Why not come down?
Saki: Tsukasa...
Saki: (He took a day off from his job to look after me.)
Saki: (I'm burdening him with this too...)
Saki: Sorry, I don't feel like eating right now.
Tsukasa's Voice: No? Well, if you get hungry, come downstairs and I'll fix up something for you anytime.
Saki: Okay...
Saki: I miss them so much...
Saki: I'm such an idiot...
Saki: I get to be with everyone, so I should be happy...
Saki: But I wanted to see the stars so much...
Saki: Huh? Did my phone just...?
Saki: Oh, that's right... If I go over there, I can see the stars.
Saki: Hello...
Saki: There's nobody here... Maybe they went to the rooftop?
Saki: Nobody here either.
Saki: Where did everyone go?
Saki: I ended up alone again...
Luka: Saki?
Saki: Oh! L-Luka!
Luka: You're wearing PJs today? That's a surprise.
Saki: Um, there's a reason for this...!
Luka: Is it also the reason why you came here on your own?
Saki: Haha, well...
Saki: You can read me like a book...
Luka: You overestimate me. There's still much I don't know about you.
Luka: But I could see that you weren't your usual self.
Saki: ...
Luka: Would you like to tell me what's wrong?
Saki: So you see, it's all my fault...
Saki: I insisted on going to the observatory together, but then I became careless and caught a cold. In the end, I just became a bother to everyone...
Saki: Which is why I've been blaming myself for this.
Luka: Why did you push yourself like that, Saki?
Luka: As Shiho said, you could go to the observatory some other time.
Saki: That's because...
Saki: I've been wanting to spend a day out with my friends like that for such a long time.
Ichika: Saki hasn't replied...
Honami: It's nice to go and visit, but what if she has gotten worse and is still cooped up in bed?
Ichika: Then we'll just pop in to say hi and leave her to rest.
Ichika: I think she's feeling very lonely today.
Shiho: Why do you say that?
Ichika: Huh?
Shiho: She was so obsessed with going out today that she got herself sick. I think Ichika understands best.
Ichika: This is just a hunch, but...
Ichika: Something she said a while ago has been nagging at me.
Shiho: A while ago?
Ichika: We visited her together once a little after she was admitted to the hospital, remember?
Shiho: Hm...? Yeah, it was a really long way to her hospital.
Honami: Her mom said they took her there to see a famous doctor specializing in her condition.
Ichika: I went to visit her several times after that with her mom.
Ichika: And I remember during one of our conversations...
Saki: Whaaat, our teacher's having a baby?! Wow, that's wonderful!
Saki: I need to write a letter and congratulate her! Do you mind taking it to her, Ichi?
Ichika: Of course.
Saki: Thanks! Now, where did I put my stationery...? Here!
Saki: “...and please take care.” There, done!
Saki: Oh, I should write to Hona and Shiho too! Letters feel much more personal than texts.
Saki: They seem so busy lately, and haven't been replying to my messages as much.
Ichika: Oh, yeah... They have a lot going on. Maybe we can visit you together soon.
Ichika: (But that's not very likely...)
Saki: Hehe... I'll draw pictures of them, too!
Saki: ...
Ichika: Saki? Is something wrong?
Saki: Oh, no...
Saki: I was just thinking... You get to go home and see everyone.
Saki: I wish I could see them, too...
Ichika: ...
Saki: Haha, gotcha! I can't let this rain get me down...
Saki: “...don't forget to write back!” There, finished!
Saki: Hona might write back, but I wonder if Shiho will bother? Hehe.
Saki: Okay, here you go. Thank you for doing this!
Ichika: No problem...
Shiho: Saki...
Honami: Poor Saki...
Ichika: She must have been much lonelier than we realized.
Ichika: So I think she'd be happy if we visited her together now.
